article.headline: Wofford 69, The Citadel 62
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- Lee Skinner had 21 points and 11 rebounds to lead Wofford to a 69-62 victory over the Citadel in the regular-season finale for both teams. Karl Cochran had 17 points and Spencer Collins 16 for the Terriers (13-18, 7-11 Southern Conference), who won three of the past four. Mike Groselle had 17 points and seven rebounds, Dylen Setzekorn scored 13 points and Raemond Robinson had 11 points and seven assists for the Bulldogs (8-21, 5-13), who have lost six of their past eight. Wofford shot 27 of 53, The Citadel 17 of 45. From an 11-9 deficit, Wofford took a 21-13 lead with 7:06 left in the first half on Taylor Wagener's layup and led 33-20 at halftime. The Bulldogs closed to 57-55 on P.J. Horgan's jumper with 5:21 remaining, but Cochran hit a 3-pointer and Spencer Collins a layup, and the Terriers held on down the stretch.
